    &lt;Title&gt;Needs Improvements&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My son had a procedure carried out at this hospital. He is 19 and this was the first time he had ever been for an operation. The first person we saw on Downing Suite ward came into the room. She didn’t introduce herself which I thought was extremely rude! She carried out routine blood pressure, temperature etc. No explanation what she was doing, and equipment was faulty. We were then left for nearly an hour without seeing anybody. My son went to theatre at 11.00  and came back at 13.20. He was observed for a couple of hours, then left. After speaking to the nurse on 2 occasions to find out when he was able to go home, we finally left at 7pm. The poor nurse on Downing Suite was run off her feet! She appeared to be the only nurse on duty, and was desperately trying to discharge patients. The hospital needs updating in the rooms and surrounding areas. It’s looking old fashioned and needs improvements. This is my local private hospital, but I would not consider using it again.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
